#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Security/Deployment-Guidelines.rst:43
msgid ""
"ROS 2 leverages DDS Security extensions to ensure security on message "
"exchanges within the same enclave. The different signed files and "
"certificates within an enclave are generated from the private keys and "
"certificates of a `Certificate Authority (CA) <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Certificate_authority>`_ trusted entity. In fact, two different CA's can be "
"selected for identity and permissions, per enclave. Those CA artifacts are "
"stored inside ``private/`` and ``public/`` sub-directories of a `Keystore "
"<https://design.ros2.org/articles/ros2_security_enclaves.html>`_ with the "
"following folder structure:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Security/Deployment-Guidelines.rst:48
msgid ""
"keystore\n"
"├── enclaves\n"
"│   └── ...\n"
"│       └── ...\n"
"├── private\n"
"│   └── ...\n"
"└── public\n"
"    └── ..."
msgstr ""

